title.narrative: PROGRAMME COORDINATION

description.narrative: By December 2018, Ministry of Health and Sanitation (MoHS) has improved capacity to provide equitable and quality integrated management of severe acute malnutrition services to children under the age of five in all districts with focus in hard to reach communities, which contributes to Policy, Guidance And Technical Support For Country Programming And Reporting, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Premises and Security
